    "The SHAP is a special adaptation of a concept coming from game theory.",
    "It measures the contribution of each explanatory variable to each prediction and can be assessed regardless of the underlying model.",
    "SHAP values that express model predictions as linear combinations of binary variables that describe whether each covariate is present in the model or not.",
    "SHAP method approximates each prediction f(x) with a g(z ′) with a linear function of binary variables z ′ ∈ {0, 1} M and quantifies φ i ∈ R defined as Eq.",
    "where is is the explanation model, z ′ is the coalition vector with 0 or 1's, M is the number of explanatory variables the maximum coalition size and φ i ∈ R is the attribute of features for the feature j i.e."
